    "Loss function Cross Entropy was chosen as our loss function, given the multi-class and binary nature of our image classifications.",
    "Its mathematical formulation is as follows 35, 55: For multi-class problems, the cross-entropy loss, L, is (Eq. 1):",
    "Here y i is the actual label and (p i) is the predicted probability for each class (i).",
    "For binary classification problem, the binary cross entropy loss, L, is computed as (Eq. 2):",
    "The optimization process strives to minimize this loss, thereby reducing the discrepancy between our model's predictions (p i) and the actual labels (y i)."
  ]
